# Cross-platform reproducibility (plan task 10b; §D.7).
# The project is authored on Windows but the path scheme, league codes, and
# football-data DD/MM/YY CSV handling are Unix-conventional, so CRLF/LF drift
# would break the byte-identical / checksum-equality acceptance criteria.
#
# Dataset checksums (ReproLog dataset_checksums, ARCH §3.2) are computed on
# NORMALIZED (LF) bytes; pinning these files to LF on checkout keeps the
# checksum sidecars and golden fixtures byte-stable across platforms.

# Default: let Git normalize line endings on commit, auto-detect text vs binary.
* text=auto

# CSV data + golden fixtures (e.g. tests/fixtures/mini_league.csv): force LF so
# checksums match the LF-normalized ReproLog hashes on every platform.
*.csv text eol=lf

# Checksum sidecars: force LF so the sidecar bytes are platform-invariant.
*.sha256 text eol=lf
